
                                            The 21-year-old allegedly confessed to strangling her son after a fight with her boyfriend.
                                         JOHANNESBURG – A KwaZulu-Natal mother accused of murdering her 11-month-old son will appear in court next week. Nomfundo Khanyile appeared in court on Tuesday on murder charges. The 21-year-old allegedly confessed to strangling her son after a fight with her boyfriend. The Director of Public Prosecution’s spokesperson Natasha Ramkisson said: “She was remanded in custody until next week on 10 October for bail investigation.”